<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<game romname="seawolf2" gamename="Seawolf II" numPlayers="2" alternating="0" mirrored="1" usesService="0" tilt="0" cocktail="0">
	<miscDetails>
The 'paddle' is actually a periscope you look through and turn. The field of view you have when looking through the scope helps you aim. Mame displays a cross hair to help you aim, you can turn it off with the F1 key.
	</miscDetails>
	<player number="1" numButtons="1">
		<controls>
			<control name="Misc">
				<constant name="other"/>
			</control>
			<control name="Paddle (Horizontal)">
				<constant name="paddle"/>
				<button name="P1_BUTTON1"/>
			</control>
		</controls>
	<labels>
			<label name="P1_BUTTON1" value="Fire Torpedo"/>
			<label name="P1_PADDLE" value="Left"/>
			<label name="P1_PADDLE_EXT" value="Right"/>
		</labels>
	</player>
</game>
